time while he was homeless. His wife would go to work,
and he would sit in his old Cadillac Brougham. One
morning, he took a ride and parked at Highland Park, in
Brooklyn. While walking around, he started collecting
bottles and cans. He made $54 and — he likes to say —
asked his pride to let him be. Since then, he has refined
